## Dependencies
- Tests (T006-T016) before implementation (T017-T050)
- T017 blocks T018, T024
- T019 blocks T020
- T021-T023 can run in parallel after T019
- T024 blocks T025, T026
- T027-T028 can run in parallel after T025-T026
- T029-T031 can run in parallel
- T032-T035 can run in parallel after T029-T031
- T036-T037 can run in parallel
- T038-T039 can run in parallel
- T040-T044 can run in parallel after respective handlers
- T045-T050 can run in parallel after API endpoints
- T051-T055 block final testing
- Implementation before polish (T056-T061)

## Parallel Example
```
# Launch T006-T010 together:
Task: "Contract test POST /api/ratings in tests/contract/test_ratings_post.cs"
Task: "Contract test PUT /api/ratings/{id} in tests/contract/test_ratings_put.cs"
Task: "Contract test DELETE /api/ratings/{id} in tests/contract/test_ratings_delete.cs"
Task: "Contract test GET /api/ratings/petwalker/{petWalkerId} in tests/contract/test_ratings_get.cs"
Task: "Contract test GET /api/ratings/petwalker/{petWalkerId}/summary in tests/contract/test_ratings_summary_get.cs"

# Launch T021-T023 together:
Task: "Create RatingAddedEvent.cs domain event"
Task: "Create RatingUpdatedEvent.cs domain event"
Task: "Create RatingRemovedEvent.cs domain event"
```

## Notes
- [P] tasks = different files, no dependencies
- Verify tests fail before implementing
- Commit after each task
- Avoid: vague tasks, same file conflicts